{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f6d21e82-b034-4c72-b446-5fbd8ab4c609","content":"You can use `dotnet watch test` with a `--filter` flag:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload).\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose fully-qualified name contains that string.\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. If you have collisions, you can be more specific (e.g., `Namespace.Class.MethodName`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"01922425-90a7-4a6b-bdf7-2ef6367b87db","outputTokens":159,"requestId":"082B:1F3FEB:871C219:95A3A9E:69EACA0E"},"id":"564c54eb-f380-4a25-a629-8d63b05690a7","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:40:36.801Z","parentId":"18b2f0b6-2904-4888-9481-9e1a1c446fe8"}
